-- 
Brazil Central Bank Says Commodity Prices Fell 0.16% in August

-- B y   E d i t o r s :   [ b n : P R S N = 1 7 1 1 1 9 8 ]   P h i l i p   S a n d e r s   [ ]
-- 
2011-09-08T15:36:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/brazil-central-bank-says-commodity-prices-fell-0-16-in-august.html
Brazil ’s central bank estimates
commodity prices fell 0.16 percent in August from July,
according to a report posted on the bank’s website today.  Commodities prices rose 18.23 percent from a year earlier,
the report said.  The index is based on a basket of international commodities
which the central bank considers most relevant to Brazilian
consumer prices.  Agricultural commodities tracked by the index include beef,
cotton, soy, wheat, sugar, corn, coffee and pork. Metals include
aluminum, iron-ore, copper, tin, zinc, lead and nickel. Energy
commodities include crude oil, natural gas and coal. 